    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-05-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-05-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="144"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d144">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 <gloss target="#t_EW1"
                    >EW</gloss>/5–2945</note>
                <head>No. 144 <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The British Minister</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BJ1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Balfour</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-05-29">May 29th,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Under Secretary</hi>:—In his telegram no. 40 to
                    the President,<note n="1" xml:id="d144fn1">
                        <ref target="#d3">Document No. 3</ref>.</note> Mr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_CMWS1">Churchill</persName> mentioned that <gloss
                        target="#t_HMG1">H. M. G.</gloss> were drawing up, as the President desired,
                    a suggested list of subjects for discussion at the next meeting of Heads of
                    Governments. Mr. <persName corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName> has now asked me to
                    forward you the enclosed list of suggested topics.<note n="2" xml:id="d144fn2"
                        >For the list referred to, see the enclosure to <ref target="#d145">document
                            No. 145</ref>.</note> I expect you will wish to inform the
                    President.</p>
                <p>Yours very sincerely,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">J. Balfour</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
